data.title: Bjorn Hansen
data.meta_description: Bjørn Hansen  is a Norwegian former football player and coach.
data.text:
Career

Hansen has been head coach and assistant coach of Rosenborg BK and is currently consultant to FK Bodø/Glimt. Bjørn Hansen played for FK Kvik, Oppdal Illinois, and Sandefjord BK. In addition to coaching Rosenborg BK both as head coach and assistant coach, he has coached the Norwegian national team (as assistant with Egil Olsen as head coach), Flatås, the Norwegian U15, U16, U17, U18, U19 and U21 teams, Kvik, Oppdal, Stjørdals-Blink and Strindheim Illinois.
